This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language understanding and the use of language to represent a hidden conceptual space. It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it presents a formal framework for studying reasoning systems. Additionally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the accuracy of systems and the use of algorithms. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies the connectivity problem in undirected graphs. Finally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the limitations of reasoning systems and the need to limit the distance between two spaces.
